<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[264,1324,283,1870]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,440,724,750]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This is a smaller and less robust species of 
<taxonomicName box="[962,1118,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Protoperigea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[962,1118,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Protoperigea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[394,582,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Protoperigea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subterminata">
<emphasis box="[394,582,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. subterminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has a slender thorax and abdomen (a, 
<figureCitation box="[1111,1200,764,790]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 21" captionStartId="43.[264,383,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[279,1312,342,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[275,1317,326,1583]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 21. Adults of the new described species: 1, Drasteria convergens. 2, Tarachidia nigra. 3, Oncocnemis duplex. 4, Oncocnemis helena. 5, Oncocnemis sala. 6, Oncocnemis kelsoensis. 7, Annaphila scurlockorum. 8, Cryphia flavipuncta. 9, Protoperigea umbricata. 10, Protoperigea subterminata. 11, Protoperigea parvulata. 12, Protoperigea calientensis. 13, Aseptis fanatica. 14, Aseptis torreyana. 15, Apamea robertsoni. 16, Apamea digitula. 17, Photedes sofiae. 18, Mammifrontia sarae. 19, Lasionycta sala. 20, Trichocerapoda harbisoni. 21, Trichocerapoda oceanis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273510/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[1170,1200,764,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) with the forewing ground color pale grayish cream and a dark reniform spot (b, 
<figureCitation box="[1157,1249,804,830]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 21" captionStartId="43.[264,383,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[279,1312,342,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[275,1317,326,1583]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 21. Adults of the new described species: 1, Drasteria convergens. 2, Tarachidia nigra. 3, Oncocnemis duplex. 4, Oncocnemis helena. 5, Oncocnemis sala. 6, Oncocnemis kelsoensis. 7, Annaphila scurlockorum. 8, Cryphia flavipuncta. 9, Protoperigea umbricata. 10, Protoperigea subterminata. 11, Protoperigea parvulata. 12, Protoperigea calientensis. 13, Aseptis fanatica. 14, Aseptis torreyana. 15, Apamea robertsoni. 16, Apamea digitula. 17, Photedes sofiae. 18, Mammifrontia sarae. 19, Lasionycta sala. 20, Trichocerapoda harbisoni. 21, Trichocerapoda oceanis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273510/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[1216,1249,804,830]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). The postmedial line is double and the area between the postmedial and the subterminal lines is dark (c, 
<figureCitation box="[364,452,884,910]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 21" captionStartId="43.[264,383,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[279,1312,342,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[275,1317,326,1583]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 21. Adults of the new described species: 1, Drasteria convergens. 2, Tarachidia nigra. 3, Oncocnemis duplex. 4, Oncocnemis helena. 5, Oncocnemis sala. 6, Oncocnemis kelsoensis. 7, Annaphila scurlockorum. 8, Cryphia flavipuncta. 9, Protoperigea umbricata. 10, Protoperigea subterminata. 11, Protoperigea parvulata. 12, Protoperigea calientensis. 13, Aseptis fanatica. 14, Aseptis torreyana. 15, Apamea robertsoni. 16, Apamea digitula. 17, Photedes sofiae. 18, Mammifrontia sarae. 19, Lasionycta sala. 20, Trichocerapoda harbisoni. 21, Trichocerapoda oceanis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273510/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[419,452,884,910]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). The species can also be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1182,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Protoperigea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subterminata">
<emphasis box="[996,1182,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. subterminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pale fuscous hindwing (d, 
<figureCitation box="[518,604,924,950]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 21" captionStartId="43.[264,383,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[279,1312,342,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[275,1317,326,1583]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 21. Adults of the new described species: 1, Drasteria convergens. 2, Tarachidia nigra. 3, Oncocnemis duplex. 4, Oncocnemis helena. 5, Oncocnemis sala. 6, Oncocnemis kelsoensis. 7, Annaphila scurlockorum. 8, Cryphia flavipuncta. 9, Protoperigea umbricata. 10, Protoperigea subterminata. 11, Protoperigea parvulata. 12, Protoperigea calientensis. 13, Aseptis fanatica. 14, Aseptis torreyana. 15, Apamea robertsoni. 16, Apamea digitula. 17, Photedes sofiae. 18, Mammifrontia sarae. 19, Lasionycta sala. 20, Trichocerapoda harbisoni. 21, Trichocerapoda oceanis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273510/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[572,604,924,950]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
); the hindwing is white in 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1101,924,949]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Protoperigea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subterminata">
<emphasis box="[917,1101,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. subterminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
