<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,284,430]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,636,323,349]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
The few known specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1030,1204,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Protoperigea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calientensis">
<emphasis box="[1030,1204,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">P. calientensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are from desert canyons around the edges of the Colorado and Mojave Deserts from the Mexican border north to Lake Tahoe. The flight period is late October–November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
